{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017q3EMcjcKziJekWkE24mre","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document of the wallet package structure:\n\n## Wallet Package Structure - Complete Exploration Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\npackages/wallet/src/\n├── balance/\n│   ├── formatBalance.ts\n│   └── index.ts\n├── mock/\n│   ├── MockWalletProvider.tsx\n│   ├── MockWalletState.ts\n│   └── index.ts\n├── real/\n│   ├── RealWalletProvider.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── test/\n│   ├── TestWalletProvider.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── transactions/\n│   └── TransactionProvider.tsx\n├── treasury/\n│   └── constants.ts\n├── context.ts\n├── hooks.ts\n├── index.ts\n├── types.ts\n├── useBalance.ts\n├── useWallet.ts\n└── WalletProvider.tsx\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. **packages/wallet/src/context.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { createContext } from \"react\";\nimport { WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\nexport const WalletContext = createContext<WalletContextValue | null>(null);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Provides the React Context for wallet state. Simple, lightweight entry point.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **packages/wallet/src/types.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey, Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport interface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n\nexport interface WalletContextValue extends WalletState {\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  /** True if using mock wallet */\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  /** Get mock balance in SOL (mock mode only) */\n  getBalance?: () => number;\n  /** Get mock balance in lamports (mock mode only) */\n  getBalanceLamports?: () => number;\n  /** Update mock balance (mock mode only) */\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Core type definitions. `WalletState` is the base connection state, and `WalletContextValue` extends it with methods and optional mock-specific helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { useContext } from \"react\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\nimport { WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(WalletContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useWallet must be used within a WalletProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Hook to access wallet context. Provides safe access with error handling if used outside provider.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **packages/wallet/src/useBalance.ts**\n```typescript\n// Polling-based balance hook with mock support\n// Features:\n// - Auto-polls on interval (default 10s)\n// - Supports mock balance (getBalanceLamports callback)\n// - Manual refresh method\n// - Formatting utilities\n// - Error handling and loading states\n\nexport interface BalanceResult {\n  balance: number | null;\n  balanceLamports: number | null;\n  loading: boolean;\n  error: Error | null;\n  refresh: () => Promise<void>;\n  formatted: string | null;\n  formattedCompact: string | null;\n  lastUpdated: Date | null;\n}\n\nexport function useBalance(options: UseBalanceOptions = {}): BalanceResult {\n  // Implementation details:\n  // - Detects mock mode via wallet.isMock flag\n  // - Uses wallet.getBalanceLamports() for mock\n  // - Fetches via RPC for real wallets\n  // - Supports custom poll interval or no polling\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Manages balance fetching with polling. Abstracts real RPC calls vs mock balance.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, lazy, Suspense } from \"react\";\nimport { MockWalletProvider } from \"./mock\";\n\nconst RealWalletProvider = lazy(() =>\n  import(\"./real/RealWalletProvider\").then((m) => ({\n    default: m.RealWalletProvider,\n  })),\n);\n\nexport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\n\ninterface WalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nfunction isMockMode(): boolean {\n  const flag =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\"\n      ? import.meta.env?.VITE_MOCK_MODE\n      : undefined;\n  // Default to mock mode when unset or explicitly \"true\"\n  return flag === undefined || flag === \"\" || flag === \"true\";\n}\n\n/**\n * Unified WalletProvider.\n * Delegates to MockWalletProvider or RealWalletProvider based on VITE_MOCK_MODE.\n */\nexport function WalletProvider({ children }: WalletProviderProps) {\n  if (isMockMode()) {\n    return <MockWalletProvider>{children}</MockWalletProvider>;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Suspense fallback={null}>\n      <RealWalletProvider>{children}</RealWalletProvider>\n    </Suspense>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Smart router that chooses between mock and real wallet based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE` env var. Lazy-loads real wallet to avoid bundling `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` in mock mode.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useCallback, useMemo } from \"react\";\nimport { Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport {\n  ConnectionProvider,\n  useConnection,\n  useWallet as useAdapterWallet,\n} from \"@solana/wallet-adapter-react\";\nimport {\n  UnifiedWalletProvider,\n  useUnifiedWalletContext,\n} from \"@jup-ag/wallet-adapter\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport type { WalletContextValue } from \"../types\";\n\nconst DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\";\n\nfunction getRpcUrl(): string {\n  const envUrl =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\" ? import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL : undefined;\n  return envUrl || DEFAULT_RPC_URL;\n}\n\nfunction getCluster(): \"devnet\" | \"testnet\" | \"mainnet-beta\" {\n  const network =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\"\n      ? import.meta.env?.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK\n      : undefined;\n  if (network === \"mainnet-beta\" || network === \"testnet\") return network;\n  return \"devnet\";\n}\n\n/**\n * Bridge component that reads from @solana/wallet-adapter-react hooks\n * and maps them to our WalletContextValue, then provides via WalletContext.\n */\nfunction WalletBridge({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n  const adapter = useAdapterWallet();\n  const { connection } = useConnection();\n  const { setShowModal } = useUnifiedWalletContext();\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    // If already connected to a wallet, just reconnect\n    if (adapter.wallet) {\n      await adapter.connect();\n      return;\n    }\n    // Otherwise open the Unified Wallet modal for wallet selection\n    setShowModal(true);\n  }, [adapter, setShowModal]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    await adapter.disconnect();\n  }, [adapter]);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!adapter.publicKey) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      const signature = await adapter.sendTransaction(transaction, connection);\n      return signature;\n    },\n    [adapter, connection],\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!adapter.signMessage) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet does not support message signing\");\n      }\n      return adapter.signMessage(message);\n    },\n    [adapter],\n  );\n\n  const value: WalletContextValue = useMemo(\n    () => ({\n      connected: adapter.connected,\n      connecting: adapter.connecting,\n      address: adapter.publicKey?.toBase58() ?? null,\n      publicKey: adapter.publicKey,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n      isMock: false,\n    }),\n    [\n      adapter.connected,\n      adapter.connecting,\n      adapter.publicKey,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n    ],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\ninterface RealWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function RealWalletProvider({ children }: RealWalletProviderProps) {\n  const endpoint = getRpcUrl();\n  const cluster = getCluster();\n\n  return (\n    <ConnectionProvider endpoint={endpoint}>\n      <UnifiedWalletProvider\n        wallets={[]}\n        config={{\n          autoConnect: true,\n          env: cluster,\n          metadata: {\n            name: \"RNG Utopia\",\n            description: \"The ultimate on-chain gaming platform\",\n            url: \"https://rngutopia.com\",\n            iconUrls: [],\n          },\n          theme: \"dark\",\n        }}\n      >\n        <WalletBridge>{children}</WalletBridge>\n      </UnifiedWalletProvider>\n    </ConnectionProvider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Production wallet integration using Jupiter's Unified Wallet Adapter. Bridges adapter hooks to our context API. Reads RPC URL and network from env vars.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  Transaction,\n  sendAndConfirmTransaction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport type { WalletContextValue } from \"../types\";\n\nconst DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n\ninterface TestWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  /** Keypair to use for signing transactions */\n  keypair: Keypair;\n  /** RPC URL (defaults to localhost:8899) */\n  rpcUrl?: string;\n  /** Auto-connect on mount (default: true) */\n  autoConnect?: boolean;\n}\n\n/**\n * Test wallet provider that signs real transactions with an injected Keypair.\n * For E2E testing against local test-validator — no browser extension needed.\n */\nexport function TestWalletProvider({\n  children,\n  keypair,\n  rpcUrl = DEFAULT_RPC_URL,\n  autoConnect = true,\n}: TestWalletProviderProps) {\n  const [connected, setConnected] = useState(false);\n  const [connecting, setConnecting] = useState(false);\n\n  const connection = useMemo(\n    () => new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\"),\n    [rpcUrl],\n  );\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setConnecting(true);\n    try {\n      // Verify the keypair works by checking if the account exists\n      await connection.getBalance(keypair.publicKey);\n      setConnected(true);\n    } finally {\n      setConnecting(false);\n    }\n  }, [connection, keypair]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setConnected(false);\n  }, []);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      transaction.feePayer = keypair.publicKey;\n      const signature = await sendAndConfirmTransaction(\n        connection,\n        transaction,\n        [keypair],\n      );\n      return signature;\n    },\n    [connected, keypair, connection],\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (_message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      // Return a deterministic signature from the keypair's secret key\n      const sig = new Uint8Array(64);\n      sig.set(keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 64));\n      return sig;\n    },\n    [connected, keypair],\n  );\n\n  // Auto-connect\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (autoConnect && !connected && !connecting) {\n      connect();\n    }\n  }, [autoConnect, connected, connecting, connect]);\n\n  const value: WalletContextValue = useMemo(\n    () => ({\n      connected,\n      connecting,\n      address: connected ? keypair.publicKey.toBase58() : null,\n      publicKey: connected ? keypair.publicKey : null,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n      isMock: false,\n    }),\n    [\n      connected,\n      connecting,\n      keypair,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n    ],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: E2E testing provider. Accepts a Keypair and connects to a local test-validator. Signs real transactions with the injected keypair (no browser extension needed).\n\n---\n\n### 8. **packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { Keypair, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport interface MockConfig {\n  initialBalance: number; // in SOL\n  autoConnect: boolean;\n  simulatedLatency: number; // ms\n  persistState: boolean;\n}\n\nexport const DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG: MockConfig = {\n  initialBalance: 1000,\n  autoConnect: false,\n  simulatedLatency: 500,\n  persistState: true,\n};\n\nconst STORAGE_KEY = \"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\";\n\ninterface PersistedState {\n  address: string;\n  balance: number; // in lamports\n}\n\nexport function createMockKeypair(): Keypair {\n  return Keypair.generate();\n}\n\nexport function loadPersistedState(): PersistedState | null {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return null;\n  try {\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);\n    if (stored) {\n      return JSON.parse(stored);\n    }\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore parse errors\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nexport function persistState(state: PersistedState): void {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(state));\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore storage errors\n  }\n}\n\nexport function clearPersistedState(): void {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore storage errors\n  }\n}\n\nexport function generateMockSignature(): string {\n  const bytes = new Uint8Array(64);\n  crypto.getRandomValues(bytes);\n  return Array.from(bytes)\n    .map((b) => b.toString(16).padStart(2, \"0\"))\n    .join(\"\");\n}\n\nexport function delay(ms: number): Promise<void> {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nexport function solToLamports(sol: number): number {\n  return Math.floor(sol * 1_000_000_000);\n}\n\nexport function lamportsToSol(lamports: number): number {\n  return lamports / 1_000_000_000;\n}\n\nexport function getPublicKeyFromAddress(address: string): PublicKey {\n  return new PublicKey(address);\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Utilities for mock wallet state management. Includes localStorage persistence, keypair generation, and formatting helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useState, useCallback, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { PublicKey, Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport { WalletContextValue, WalletState } from \"../types\";\nimport {\n  MockConfig,\n  DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG,\n  createMockKeypair,\n  loadPersistedState,\n  persistState,\n  clearPersistedState,\n  generateMockSignature,\n  delay,\n  solToLamports,\n  lamportsToSol,\n  getPublicKeyFromAddress,\n} from \"./MockWalletState\";\n\ninterface MockWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  config?: Partial<MockConfig>;\n}\n\nconst initialState: WalletState = {\n  connected: false,\n  connecting: false,\n  address: null,\n  publicKey: null,\n};\n\nexport function MockWalletProvider({\n  children,\n  config: userConfig,\n}: MockWalletProviderProps) {\n  const config: MockConfig = { ...DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG, ...userConfig };\n\n  const [state, setState] = useState<WalletState>(initialState);\n  const [balanceLamports, setBalanceLamports] = useState<number>(\n    solToLamports(config.initialBalance)\n  );\n\n  // Load persisted state on mount\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (config.persistState) {\n      const persisted = loadPersistedState();\n      if (persisted) {\n        setBalanceLamports(persisted.balance);\n        if (config.autoConnect) {\n          const pubKey = getPublicKeyFromAddress(persisted.address);\n          setState({\n            connected: true,\n            connecting: false,\n            address: persisted.address,\n            publicKey: pubKey,\n          });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }, [config.persistState, config.autoConnect]);\n\n  // Persist state changes\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (config.persistState && state.connected && state.address) {\n      persistState({\n        address: state.address,\n        balance: balanceLamports,\n      });\n    }\n  }, [config.persistState, state.connected, state.address, balanceLamports]);\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setState((prev) => ({ ...prev, connecting: true }));\n\n    try {\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency);\n\n      // Check for persisted state first\n      const persisted = loadPersistedState();\n      let address: string;\n      let pubKey: PublicKey;\n\n      if (persisted) {\n        address = persisted.address;\n        pubKey = getPublicKeyFromAddress(address);\n        setBalanceLamports(solToLamports(config.initialBalance));\n      } else {\n        // Generate new mock keypair\n        const keypair = createMockKeypair();\n        address = keypair.publicKey.toBase58();\n        pubKey = keypair.publicKey;\n        setBalanceLamports(solToLamports(config.initialBalance));\n      }\n\n      setState({\n        connected: true,\n        connecting: false,\n        address,\n        publicKey: pubKey,\n      });\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Mock wallet connect failed:\", error);\n      setState((prev) => ({ ...prev, connecting: false }));\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }, [config.simulatedLatency, config.initialBalance]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    await delay(config.simulatedLatency / 2);\n\n    if (!config.persistState) {\n      clearPersistedState();\n    }\n\n    setState(initialState);\n  }, [config.simulatedLatency, config.persistState]);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (_transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!state.connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency);\n\n      // Simulate random failure (5% chance)\n      if (Math.random() < 0.05) {\n        throw new Error(\"Mock transaction simulation failed\");\n      }\n\n      // Return mock signature\n      return generateMockSignature();\n    },\n    [state.connected, config.simulatedLatency]\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (_message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!state.connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency / 2);\n\n      // Return mock signature (64 bytes)\n      const mockSig = new Uint8Array(64);\n      crypto.getRandomValues(mockSig);\n      return mockSig;\n    },\n    [state.connected, config.simulatedLatency]\n  );\n\n  // Expose balance management for mock transactions\n  const updateBalance = useCallback((deltaLamports: number) => {\n    setBalanceLamports((prev) => Math.max(0, prev + deltaLamports));\n  }, []);\n\n  const getBalance = useCallback(() => {\n    return lamportsToSol(balanceLamports);\n  }, [balanceLamports]);\n\n  const getBalanceLamports = useCallback(() => {\n    return balanceLamports;\n  }, [balanceLamports]);\n\n  // Extended context value with mock-specific methods\n  const value: WalletContextValue & {\n    updateBalance: (deltaLamports: number) => void;\n    getBalance: () => number;\n    getBalanceLamports: () => number;\n    isMock: boolean;\n  } = {\n    ...state,\n    connect,\n    disconnect,\n    sendTransaction,\n    signMessage,\n    updateBalance,\n    getBalance,\n    getBalanceLamports,\n    isMock: true,\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Full mock wallet implementation. Features localStorage persistence, simulated latency, 5% failure rate, and balance management. Defaults to mock mode.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **packages/wallet/src/transactions/TransactionProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport {\n  ReactNode,\n  createContext,\n  useContext,\n  useState,\n  useCallback,\n} from \"react\";\nimport { Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { useWallet } from \"../useWallet\";\n\nexport type TransactionStatus =\n  | \"idle\"\n  | \"building\"\n  | \"signing\"\n  | \"submitting\"\n  | \"confirming\"\n  | \"confirmed\"\n  | \"failed\";\n\nexport interface TransactionState {\n  status: TransactionStatus;\n  signature: string | null;\n  error: Error | null;\n}\n\nexport interface TransactionContextValue {\n  state: TransactionState;\n  submit: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  reset: () => void;\n  isProcessing: boolean;\n}\n\nconst TransactionContext = createContext<TransactionContextValue | null>(null);\n\nconst initialState: TransactionState = {\n  status: \"idle\",\n  signature: null,\n  error: null,\n};\n\ninterface TransactionProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function TransactionProvider({ children }: TransactionProviderProps) {\n  const { sendTransaction } = useWallet();\n  const [state, setState] = useState<TransactionState>(initialState);\n\n  const submit = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      setState({ status: \"signing\", signature: null, error: null });\n\n      try {\n        setState((s) => ({ ...s, status: \"submitting\" }));\n        const signature = await sendTransaction(transaction);\n\n        setState((s) => ({ ...s, status: \"confirming\" }));\n        // In real implementation, we'd wait for confirmation here\n\n        setState({ status: \"confirmed\", signature, error: null });\n        return signature;\n      } catch (error) {\n        const err = error instanceof Error ? error : new Error(String(error));\n        setState({ status: \"failed\", signature: null, error: err });\n        throw err;\n      }\n    },\n    [sendTransaction]\n  );\n\n  const reset = useCallback(() => {\n    setState(initialState);\n  }, []);\n\n  const isProcessing =\n    state.status !== \"idle\" &&\n    state.status !== \"confirmed\" &&\n    state.status !== \"failed\";\n\n  const value: TransactionContextValue = {\n    state,\n    submit,\n    reset,\n    isProcessing,\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <TransactionContext.Provider value={value}>\n      {children}\n    </TransactionContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\nexport function useTransaction(): TransactionContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(TransactionContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useTransaction must be used within TransactionProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Transaction state management provider. Tracks submission, signing, confirming, and final states. Includes error tracking and processing flag.\n\n---\n\n### 11. **packages/wallet/src/balance/formatBalance.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { LAMPORTS_PER_SOL } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n/**\n * Format lamports to a display amount with specified precision\n */\nexport function formatAmount(lamports: number | bigint, precision = 2): string {\n  const sol = Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  return sol.toFixed(precision);\n}\n\n/**\n * Format balance in compact form (e.g., 1.2k for 1200)\n */\nexport function formatAmountCompact(lamports: number | bigint): string {\n  const sol = Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  if (sol >= 1_000_000) return `${(sol / 1_000_000).toFixed(1)}M`;\n  if (sol >= 1000) return `${(sol / 1000).toFixed(1)}k`;\n  if (sol >= 1) return sol.toFixed(2);\n  if (sol >= 0.01) return sol.toFixed(3);\n  return sol.toFixed(4);\n}\n\n/**\n * Convert lamports to SOL\n * @legacy Kept for wallet internals that still use lamport conversion\n */\nexport function lamportsToSOL(lamports: number | bigint): number {\n  return Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n}\n\n/**\n * Convert SOL to lamports\n */\nexport function SOLToLamports(sol: number): bigint {\n  return BigInt(Math.floor(sol * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL));\n}\n\n/**\n * Format a balance for display with $ prefix\n */\nexport function formatBalanceDisplay(\n  lamports: number | bigint | null,\n  options: {\n    precision?: number;\n    showSymbol?: boolean;\n    compact?: boolean;\n  } = {}\n): string {\n  const { precision = 4, showSymbol = true, compact = false } = options;\n\n  if (lamports === null) {\n    return showSymbol ? \"$-.----\" : \"-.----\";\n  }\n\n  const formatted = compact\n    ? formatAmountCompact(lamports)\n    : formatAmount(lamports, precision);\n\n  return showSymbol ? `$${formatted}` : formatted;\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse a dollar amount string to lamports\n * Returns null if invalid\n */\nexport function parseSOLInput(input: string): bigint | null {\n  const trimmed = input.trim().replace(/,/g, \"\");\n  const value = parseFloat(trimmed);\n\n  if (isNaN(value) || value < 0) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return SOLToLamports(value);\n}\n\n/**\n * Validate if a string is a valid amount\n */\nexport function isValidSOLAmount(input: string): boolean {\n  return parseSOLInput(input) !== null;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Balance formatting utilities. Handles SOL/lamports conversion, compact display formats, and input parsing/validation.\n\n---\n\n### 12. **packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n// Fee constants (from ARCHITECTURE.md)\nexport const FEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  /** Total fee in basis points (300 = 3%) */\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,\n  /** Platform revenue in basis points (200 = 2%) */\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200,\n  /** Cashback pool in basis points (50 = 0.5%) */\n  CASHBACK_POOL_BPS: 50,\n  /** Rewards budget in basis points (50 = 0.5%) */\n  REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS: 50,\n} as const;\n\n// Fee breakdown for display\nexport const FEE_BREAKDOWN = {\n  total: { bps: 300, display: \"3%\" },\n  platformRevenue: { bps: 200, display: \"2%\" },\n  cashbackPool: { bps: 50, display: \"0.5%\" },\n  rewardsBudget: { bps: 50, display: \"0.5%\" },\n} as const;\n\n// Hard limits from architecture (cannot be changed on-chain)\nexport const LIMITS = {\n  /** Maximum fee in basis points (1000 = 10%) */\n  MAX_FEE_BPS: 1000,\n  /** Maximum bet in lamports (1000 SOL) */\n  MAX_BET_LAMPORTS: 1_000_000_000_000n,\n  /** Maximum players per round */\n  MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND: 10_000,\n} as const;\n\n// Placeholder program IDs - update with deployed addresses\nexport const PROGRAM_IDS = {\n  /** Pool manager program ID */\n  POOL_MANAGER: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  /** VRF consumer program ID */\n  VRF_CONSUMER: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  /** Game config program ID */\n  GAME_CONFIG: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n} as const;\n\n// Treasury addresses - update with deployed addresses\nexport const TREASURY_ADDRESSES = {\n  mainnet: {\n    treasury: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    rakeback: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    referral: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  },\n  devnet: {\n    treasury: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    rakeback: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    referral: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  },\n} as const;\n\n/**\n * Calculate fee amount from pool total\n */\nexport function calculateFee(poolTotalLamports: bigint): bigint {\n  return (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.TOTAL_BPS)) / 10000n;\n}\n\n/**\n * Calculate winner payout from pool total (after fees)\n */\nexport function calculatePayout(poolTotalLamports: bigint): bigint {\n  const fee = calculateFee(poolTotalLamports);\n  return poolTotalLamports - fee;\n}\n\n/**\n * Calculate fee breakdown from pool total\n */\nexport function calculateFeeBreakdown(poolTotalLamports: bigint): {\n  total: bigint;\n  platformRevenue: bigint;\n  cashbackPool: bigint;\n  rewardsBudget: bigint;\n} {\n  const total = calculateFee(poolTotalLamports);\n  const platformRevenue =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS)) / 10000n;\n  const cashbackPool =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.CASHBACK_POOL_BPS)) / 10000n;\n  const rewardsBudget =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS)) / 10000n;\n\n  return {\n    total,\n    platformRevenue,\n    cashbackPool,\n    rewardsBudget,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Treasury and fee configuration. Defines V1 3% fee split, limits, program IDs, and treasury addresses. Includes fee calculation helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 13. **packages/wallet/package.json**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/wallet\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n    \"./mock\": \"./src/mock/index.ts\",\n    \"./real\": \"./src/real/index.ts\",\n    \"./test\": \"./src/test/index.ts\",\n    \"./context\": \"./src/context.ts\",\n    \"./hooks\": {\n      \"import\": \"./src/hooks.ts\",\n      \"types\": \"./src/hooks.ts\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@jup-ag/wallet-adapter\": \"^0.2.6\",\n    \"@solana/wallet-adapter-base\": \"^0.9.23\",\n    \"@solana/wallet-adapter-react\": \"^0.15.35\",\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.3.1\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/react\": \"^18.3.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vite\": \"^6.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"peerDependencies\": {\n    \"react\": \"^18.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Package metadata and dependencies. Key exports allow selective imports (mock, real, test, hooks, context).\n\n---\n\n### 14. **packages/wallet/src/hooks.ts**\n```typescript\n// Lightweight hooks entry point - no provider dependencies\nexport { useWallet } from \"./useWallet\";\nexport { useBalance } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { BalanceResult } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { WalletState, WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Clean hooks export path. No provider dependencies, lightweight imports.\n\n---\n\n### 15. **packages/wallet/src/index.ts**\n```typescript\n// Context (standalone - no provider dependencies)\nexport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\n\n// Core hooks (import context, not providers)\nexport { useWallet } from \"./useWallet\";\nexport { useBalance } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { WalletState, WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\n// Mock wallet exports (lightweight - no adapter dependency)\nexport { MockWalletProvider, DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG } from \"./mock\";\nexport type { MockConfig } from \"./mock\";\n\n// Real wallet exports (lazy-loaded via WalletProvider, or direct import)\nexport { RealWalletProvider } from \"./real\";\n\n// Test wallet exports (for E2E against local test-validator)\nexport { TestWalletProvider } from \"./test\";\n\n// Full wallet provider\nexport { WalletProvider } from \"./WalletProvider\";\n\n// Balance utilities\nexport { solToLamports, lamportsToSol } from \"./mock\";\nexport {\n  formatAmount,\n  formatAmountCompact,\n  lamportsToSOL,\n  SOLToLamports,\n  formatBalanceDisplay,\n  parseSOLInput,\n  isValidSOLAmount,\n} from \"./balance\";\nexport type { BalanceResult } from \"./useBalance\";\n\n// Transaction management\nexport {\n  TransactionProvider,\n  useTransaction,\n} from \"./transactions\";\nexport type {\n  TransactionState,\n  TransactionStatus,\n  TransactionContextValue,\n} from \"./transactions\";\n\n// Treasury utilities\nexport {\n  FEE_CONSTANTS,\n  FEE_BREAKDOWN,\n  LIMITS,\n  PROGRAM_IDS,\n  TREASURY_ADDRESSES,\n  calculateFee,\n  calculatePayout,\n  calculateFeeBreakdown,\n} from \"./treasury\";\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Main export barrel. Carefully curated to allow tree-shaking and selective imports.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architecture Insights\n\n1. **Three Wallet Modes**:\n   - **Mock** (default): Fully in-memory, no RPC needed, persists to localStorage\n   - **Real**: Jupiter Unified Wallet Adapter, real RPC connection\n   - **Test**: Hardwired Keypair for E2E testing against local validator\n\n2. **Environment-Driven Switching**:\n   - `VITE_MOCK_MODE` (defaults to `true`) controls router\n   - `VITE_RPC_URL` for real wallet RPC endpoint\n   - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` for cluster selection (defaults to devnet)\n\n3. **Context Pattern**:\n   - Single `WalletContext` shared across all providers\n   - Minimal interface (`WalletContextValue`)\n   - Hooks (`useWallet`, `useBalance`) provide safe access\n\n4. **Balance Polling**:\n   - Automatic polling (configurable interval)\n   - Supports both mock and real wallets\n   - Manual refresh method\n\n5. **Transaction Tracking**:\n   - State machine (`idle` → `signing` → `submitting` → `confirming` → `confirmed`/`failed`)\n   - Separate provider for async transaction submission\n\n6. **Treasury Constants**:\n   - 3% total fee (2% platform, 0.5% cashback, 0.5% rewards)\n   - Placeholder program IDs and addresses (pending deployment)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a38a207 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 49470\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 75732</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dcb8cfea-3149-4f02-a81d-4deae733513a","uuid":"f2157d4d-ec65-48dd-afa3-ae417510b35a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the wallet package structure at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/. I need to understand:\n1. Full file listing of the packages/wallet/src/ directory (including subdirectories)\n2. Contents of packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx\n3. Contents of packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx\n4. Contents of packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx\n5. Contents of packages/wallet/src/types.ts\n6. Contents of packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts\n7. Contents of packages/wallet/src/useBalance.ts\n8. Contents of packages/wallet/src/context.ts\n9. Contents of packages/wallet/package.json\n\nReturn all file contents in full.","agentId":"a38a207","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document of the wallet package structure:\n\n## Wallet Package Structure - Complete Exploration Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\npackages/wallet/src/\n├── balance/\n│   ├── formatBalance.ts\n│   └── index.ts\n├── mock/\n│   ├── MockWalletProvider.tsx\n│   ├── MockWalletState.ts\n│   └── index.ts\n├── real/\n│   ├── RealWalletProvider.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── test/\n│   ├── TestWalletProvider.tsx\n│   └── index.ts\n├── transactions/\n│   └── TransactionProvider.tsx\n├── treasury/\n│   └── constants.ts\n├── context.ts\n├── hooks.ts\n├── index.ts\n├── types.ts\n├── useBalance.ts\n├── useWallet.ts\n└── WalletProvider.tsx\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. **packages/wallet/src/context.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { createContext } from \"react\";\nimport { WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\nexport const WalletContext = createContext<WalletContextValue | null>(null);\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Provides the React Context for wallet state. Simple, lightweight entry point.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **packages/wallet/src/types.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey, Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport interface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n\nexport interface WalletContextValue extends WalletState {\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  /** True if using mock wallet */\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  /** Get mock balance in SOL (mock mode only) */\n  getBalance?: () => number;\n  /** Get mock balance in lamports (mock mode only) */\n  getBalanceLamports?: () => number;\n  /** Update mock balance (mock mode only) */\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Core type definitions. `WalletState` is the base connection state, and `WalletContextValue` extends it with methods and optional mock-specific helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { useContext } from \"react\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\nimport { WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(WalletContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useWallet must be used within a WalletProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Hook to access wallet context. Provides safe access with error handling if used outside provider.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **packages/wallet/src/useBalance.ts**\n```typescript\n// Polling-based balance hook with mock support\n// Features:\n// - Auto-polls on interval (default 10s)\n// - Supports mock balance (getBalanceLamports callback)\n// - Manual refresh method\n// - Formatting utilities\n// - Error handling and loading states\n\nexport interface BalanceResult {\n  balance: number | null;\n  balanceLamports: number | null;\n  loading: boolean;\n  error: Error | null;\n  refresh: () => Promise<void>;\n  formatted: string | null;\n  formattedCompact: string | null;\n  lastUpdated: Date | null;\n}\n\nexport function useBalance(options: UseBalanceOptions = {}): BalanceResult {\n  // Implementation details:\n  // - Detects mock mode via wallet.isMock flag\n  // - Uses wallet.getBalanceLamports() for mock\n  // - Fetches via RPC for real wallets\n  // - Supports custom poll interval or no polling\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Manages balance fetching with polling. Abstracts real RPC calls vs mock balance.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, lazy, Suspense } from \"react\";\nimport { MockWalletProvider } from \"./mock\";\n\nconst RealWalletProvider = lazy(() =>\n  import(\"./real/RealWalletProvider\").then((m) => ({\n    default: m.RealWalletProvider,\n  })),\n);\n\nexport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\n\ninterface WalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nfunction isMockMode(): boolean {\n  const flag =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\"\n      ? import.meta.env?.VITE_MOCK_MODE\n      : undefined;\n  // Default to mock mode when unset or explicitly \"true\"\n  return flag === undefined || flag === \"\" || flag === \"true\";\n}\n\n/**\n * Unified WalletProvider.\n * Delegates to MockWalletProvider or RealWalletProvider based on VITE_MOCK_MODE.\n */\nexport function WalletProvider({ children }: WalletProviderProps) {\n  if (isMockMode()) {\n    return <MockWalletProvider>{children}</MockWalletProvider>;\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <Suspense fallback={null}>\n      <RealWalletProvider>{children}</RealWalletProvider>\n    </Suspense>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Smart router that chooses between mock and real wallet based on `VITE_MOCK_MODE` env var. Lazy-loads real wallet to avoid bundling `@jup-ag/wallet-adapter` in mock mode.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useCallback, useMemo } from \"react\";\nimport { Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport {\n  ConnectionProvider,\n  useConnection,\n  useWallet as useAdapterWallet,\n} from \"@solana/wallet-adapter-react\";\nimport {\n  UnifiedWalletProvider,\n  useUnifiedWalletContext,\n} from \"@jup-ag/wallet-adapter\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport type { WalletContextValue } from \"../types\";\n\nconst DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\";\n\nfunction getRpcUrl(): string {\n  const envUrl =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\" ? import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL : undefined;\n  return envUrl || DEFAULT_RPC_URL;\n}\n\nfunction getCluster(): \"devnet\" | \"testnet\" | \"mainnet-beta\" {\n  const network =\n    typeof import.meta !== \"undefined\"\n      ? import.meta.env?.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK\n      : undefined;\n  if (network === \"mainnet-beta\" || network === \"testnet\") return network;\n  return \"devnet\";\n}\n\n/**\n * Bridge component that reads from @solana/wallet-adapter-react hooks\n * and maps them to our WalletContextValue, then provides via WalletContext.\n */\nfunction WalletBridge({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n  const adapter = useAdapterWallet();\n  const { connection } = useConnection();\n  const { setShowModal } = useUnifiedWalletContext();\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    // If already connected to a wallet, just reconnect\n    if (adapter.wallet) {\n      await adapter.connect();\n      return;\n    }\n    // Otherwise open the Unified Wallet modal for wallet selection\n    setShowModal(true);\n  }, [adapter, setShowModal]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    await adapter.disconnect();\n  }, [adapter]);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!adapter.publicKey) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      const signature = await adapter.sendTransaction(transaction, connection);\n      return signature;\n    },\n    [adapter, connection],\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!adapter.signMessage) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet does not support message signing\");\n      }\n      return adapter.signMessage(message);\n    },\n    [adapter],\n  );\n\n  const value: WalletContextValue = useMemo(\n    () => ({\n      connected: adapter.connected,\n      connecting: adapter.connecting,\n      address: adapter.publicKey?.toBase58() ?? null,\n      publicKey: adapter.publicKey,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n      isMock: false,\n    }),\n    [\n      adapter.connected,\n      adapter.connecting,\n      adapter.publicKey,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n    ],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\ninterface RealWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function RealWalletProvider({ children }: RealWalletProviderProps) {\n  const endpoint = getRpcUrl();\n  const cluster = getCluster();\n\n  return (\n    <ConnectionProvider endpoint={endpoint}>\n      <UnifiedWalletProvider\n        wallets={[]}\n        config={{\n          autoConnect: true,\n          env: cluster,\n          metadata: {\n            name: \"RNG Utopia\",\n            description: \"The ultimate on-chain gaming platform\",\n            url: \"https://rngutopia.com\",\n            iconUrls: [],\n          },\n          theme: \"dark\",\n        }}\n      >\n        <WalletBridge>{children}</WalletBridge>\n      </UnifiedWalletProvider>\n    </ConnectionProvider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Production wallet integration using Jupiter's Unified Wallet Adapter. Bridges adapter hooks to our context API. Reads RPC URL and network from env vars.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  Transaction,\n  sendAndConfirmTransaction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport type { WalletContextValue } from \"../types\";\n\nconst DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n\ninterface TestWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  /** Keypair to use for signing transactions */\n  keypair: Keypair;\n  /** RPC URL (defaults to localhost:8899) */\n  rpcUrl?: string;\n  /** Auto-connect on mount (default: true) */\n  autoConnect?: boolean;\n}\n\n/**\n * Test wallet provider that signs real transactions with an injected Keypair.\n * For E2E testing against local test-validator — no browser extension needed.\n */\nexport function TestWalletProvider({\n  children,\n  keypair,\n  rpcUrl = DEFAULT_RPC_URL,\n  autoConnect = true,\n}: TestWalletProviderProps) {\n  const [connected, setConnected] = useState(false);\n  const [connecting, setConnecting] = useState(false);\n\n  const connection = useMemo(\n    () => new Connection(rpcUrl, \"confirmed\"),\n    [rpcUrl],\n  );\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setConnecting(true);\n    try {\n      // Verify the keypair works by checking if the account exists\n      await connection.getBalance(keypair.publicKey);\n      setConnected(true);\n    } finally {\n      setConnecting(false);\n    }\n  }, [connection, keypair]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setConnected(false);\n  }, []);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      transaction.feePayer = keypair.publicKey;\n      const signature = await sendAndConfirmTransaction(\n        connection,\n        transaction,\n        [keypair],\n      );\n      return signature;\n    },\n    [connected, keypair, connection],\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (_message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n      // Return a deterministic signature from the keypair's secret key\n      const sig = new Uint8Array(64);\n      sig.set(keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 64));\n      return sig;\n    },\n    [connected, keypair],\n  );\n\n  // Auto-connect\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (autoConnect && !connected && !connecting) {\n      connect();\n    }\n  }, [autoConnect, connected, connecting, connect]);\n\n  const value: WalletContextValue = useMemo(\n    () => ({\n      connected,\n      connecting,\n      address: connected ? keypair.publicKey.toBase58() : null,\n      publicKey: connected ? keypair.publicKey : null,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n      isMock: false,\n    }),\n    [\n      connected,\n      connecting,\n      keypair,\n      connect,\n      disconnect,\n      sendTransaction,\n      signMessage,\n    ],\n  );\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: E2E testing provider. Accepts a Keypair and connects to a local test-validator. Signs real transactions with the injected keypair (no browser extension needed).\n\n---\n\n### 8. **packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletState.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { Keypair, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport interface MockConfig {\n  initialBalance: number; // in SOL\n  autoConnect: boolean;\n  simulatedLatency: number; // ms\n  persistState: boolean;\n}\n\nexport const DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG: MockConfig = {\n  initialBalance: 1000,\n  autoConnect: false,\n  simulatedLatency: 500,\n  persistState: true,\n};\n\nconst STORAGE_KEY = \"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\";\n\ninterface PersistedState {\n  address: string;\n  balance: number; // in lamports\n}\n\nexport function createMockKeypair(): Keypair {\n  return Keypair.generate();\n}\n\nexport function loadPersistedState(): PersistedState | null {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return null;\n  try {\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);\n    if (stored) {\n      return JSON.parse(stored);\n    }\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore parse errors\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nexport function persistState(state: PersistedState): void {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, JSON.stringify(state));\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore storage errors\n  }\n}\n\nexport function clearPersistedState(): void {\n  if (typeof window === \"undefined\") return;\n  try {\n    localStorage.removeItem(STORAGE_KEY);\n  } catch {\n    // Ignore storage errors\n  }\n}\n\nexport function generateMockSignature(): string {\n  const bytes = new Uint8Array(64);\n  crypto.getRandomValues(bytes);\n  return Array.from(bytes)\n    .map((b) => b.toString(16).padStart(2, \"0\"))\n    .join(\"\");\n}\n\nexport function delay(ms: number): Promise<void> {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nexport function solToLamports(sol: number): number {\n  return Math.floor(sol * 1_000_000_000);\n}\n\nexport function lamportsToSol(lamports: number): number {\n  return lamports / 1_000_000_000;\n}\n\nexport function getPublicKeyFromAddress(address: string): PublicKey {\n  return new PublicKey(address);\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Utilities for mock wallet state management. Includes localStorage persistence, keypair generation, and formatting helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **packages/wallet/src/mock/MockWalletProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport { ReactNode, useState, useCallback, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { PublicKey, Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"../context\";\nimport { WalletContextValue, WalletState } from \"../types\";\nimport {\n  MockConfig,\n  DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG,\n  createMockKeypair,\n  loadPersistedState,\n  persistState,\n  clearPersistedState,\n  generateMockSignature,\n  delay,\n  solToLamports,\n  lamportsToSol,\n  getPublicKeyFromAddress,\n} from \"./MockWalletState\";\n\ninterface MockWalletProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  config?: Partial<MockConfig>;\n}\n\nconst initialState: WalletState = {\n  connected: false,\n  connecting: false,\n  address: null,\n  publicKey: null,\n};\n\nexport function MockWalletProvider({\n  children,\n  config: userConfig,\n}: MockWalletProviderProps) {\n  const config: MockConfig = { ...DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG, ...userConfig };\n\n  const [state, setState] = useState<WalletState>(initialState);\n  const [balanceLamports, setBalanceLamports] = useState<number>(\n    solToLamports(config.initialBalance)\n  );\n\n  // Load persisted state on mount\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (config.persistState) {\n      const persisted = loadPersistedState();\n      if (persisted) {\n        setBalanceLamports(persisted.balance);\n        if (config.autoConnect) {\n          const pubKey = getPublicKeyFromAddress(persisted.address);\n          setState({\n            connected: true,\n            connecting: false,\n            address: persisted.address,\n            publicKey: pubKey,\n          });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }, [config.persistState, config.autoConnect]);\n\n  // Persist state changes\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (config.persistState && state.connected && state.address) {\n      persistState({\n        address: state.address,\n        balance: balanceLamports,\n      });\n    }\n  }, [config.persistState, state.connected, state.address, balanceLamports]);\n\n  const connect = useCallback(async () => {\n    setState((prev) => ({ ...prev, connecting: true }));\n\n    try {\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency);\n\n      // Check for persisted state first\n      const persisted = loadPersistedState();\n      let address: string;\n      let pubKey: PublicKey;\n\n      if (persisted) {\n        address = persisted.address;\n        pubKey = getPublicKeyFromAddress(address);\n        setBalanceLamports(solToLamports(config.initialBalance));\n      } else {\n        // Generate new mock keypair\n        const keypair = createMockKeypair();\n        address = keypair.publicKey.toBase58();\n        pubKey = keypair.publicKey;\n        setBalanceLamports(solToLamports(config.initialBalance));\n      }\n\n      setState({\n        connected: true,\n        connecting: false,\n        address,\n        publicKey: pubKey,\n      });\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error(\"Mock wallet connect failed:\", error);\n      setState((prev) => ({ ...prev, connecting: false }));\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }, [config.simulatedLatency, config.initialBalance]);\n\n  const disconnect = useCallback(async () => {\n    await delay(config.simulatedLatency / 2);\n\n    if (!config.persistState) {\n      clearPersistedState();\n    }\n\n    setState(initialState);\n  }, [config.simulatedLatency, config.persistState]);\n\n  const sendTransaction = useCallback(\n    async (_transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      if (!state.connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency);\n\n      // Simulate random failure (5% chance)\n      if (Math.random() < 0.05) {\n        throw new Error(\"Mock transaction simulation failed\");\n      }\n\n      // Return mock signature\n      return generateMockSignature();\n    },\n    [state.connected, config.simulatedLatency]\n  );\n\n  const signMessage = useCallback(\n    async (_message: Uint8Array): Promise<Uint8Array> => {\n      if (!state.connected) {\n        throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n      }\n\n      await delay(config.simulatedLatency / 2);\n\n      // Return mock signature (64 bytes)\n      const mockSig = new Uint8Array(64);\n      crypto.getRandomValues(mockSig);\n      return mockSig;\n    },\n    [state.connected, config.simulatedLatency]\n  );\n\n  // Expose balance management for mock transactions\n  const updateBalance = useCallback((deltaLamports: number) => {\n    setBalanceLamports((prev) => Math.max(0, prev + deltaLamports));\n  }, []);\n\n  const getBalance = useCallback(() => {\n    return lamportsToSol(balanceLamports);\n  }, [balanceLamports]);\n\n  const getBalanceLamports = useCallback(() => {\n    return balanceLamports;\n  }, [balanceLamports]);\n\n  // Extended context value with mock-specific methods\n  const value: WalletContextValue & {\n    updateBalance: (deltaLamports: number) => void;\n    getBalance: () => number;\n    getBalanceLamports: () => number;\n    isMock: boolean;\n  } = {\n    ...state,\n    connect,\n    disconnect,\n    sendTransaction,\n    signMessage,\n    updateBalance,\n    getBalance,\n    getBalanceLamports,\n    isMock: true,\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <WalletContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</WalletContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Full mock wallet implementation. Features localStorage persistence, simulated latency, 5% failure rate, and balance management. Defaults to mock mode.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **packages/wallet/src/transactions/TransactionProvider.tsx**\n```typescript\nimport {\n  ReactNode,\n  createContext,\n  useContext,\n  useState,\n  useCallback,\n} from \"react\";\nimport { Transaction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { useWallet } from \"../useWallet\";\n\nexport type TransactionStatus =\n  | \"idle\"\n  | \"building\"\n  | \"signing\"\n  | \"submitting\"\n  | \"confirming\"\n  | \"confirmed\"\n  | \"failed\";\n\nexport interface TransactionState {\n  status: TransactionStatus;\n  signature: string | null;\n  error: Error | null;\n}\n\nexport interface TransactionContextValue {\n  state: TransactionState;\n  submit: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  reset: () => void;\n  isProcessing: boolean;\n}\n\nconst TransactionContext = createContext<TransactionContextValue | null>(null);\n\nconst initialState: TransactionState = {\n  status: \"idle\",\n  signature: null,\n  error: null,\n};\n\ninterface TransactionProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function TransactionProvider({ children }: TransactionProviderProps) {\n  const { sendTransaction } = useWallet();\n  const [state, setState] = useState<TransactionState>(initialState);\n\n  const submit = useCallback(\n    async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n      setState({ status: \"signing\", signature: null, error: null });\n\n      try {\n        setState((s) => ({ ...s, status: \"submitting\" }));\n        const signature = await sendTransaction(transaction);\n\n        setState((s) => ({ ...s, status: \"confirming\" }));\n        // In real implementation, we'd wait for confirmation here\n\n        setState({ status: \"confirmed\", signature, error: null });\n        return signature;\n      } catch (error) {\n        const err = error instanceof Error ? error : new Error(String(error));\n        setState({ status: \"failed\", signature: null, error: err });\n        throw err;\n      }\n    },\n    [sendTransaction]\n  );\n\n  const reset = useCallback(() => {\n    setState(initialState);\n  }, []);\n\n  const isProcessing =\n    state.status !== \"idle\" &&\n    state.status !== \"confirmed\" &&\n    state.status !== \"failed\";\n\n  const value: TransactionContextValue = {\n    state,\n    submit,\n    reset,\n    isProcessing,\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <TransactionContext.Provider value={value}>\n      {children}\n    </TransactionContext.Provider>\n  );\n}\n\nexport function useTransaction(): TransactionContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(TransactionContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useTransaction must be used within TransactionProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Transaction state management provider. Tracks submission, signing, confirming, and final states. Includes error tracking and processing flag.\n\n---\n\n### 11. **packages/wallet/src/balance/formatBalance.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { LAMPORTS_PER_SOL } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n/**\n * Format lamports to a display amount with specified precision\n */\nexport function formatAmount(lamports: number | bigint, precision = 2): string {\n  const sol = Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  return sol.toFixed(precision);\n}\n\n/**\n * Format balance in compact form (e.g., 1.2k for 1200)\n */\nexport function formatAmountCompact(lamports: number | bigint): string {\n  const sol = Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n  if (sol >= 1_000_000) return `${(sol / 1_000_000).toFixed(1)}M`;\n  if (sol >= 1000) return `${(sol / 1000).toFixed(1)}k`;\n  if (sol >= 1) return sol.toFixed(2);\n  if (sol >= 0.01) return sol.toFixed(3);\n  return sol.toFixed(4);\n}\n\n/**\n * Convert lamports to SOL\n * @legacy Kept for wallet internals that still use lamport conversion\n */\nexport function lamportsToSOL(lamports: number | bigint): number {\n  return Number(lamports) / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL;\n}\n\n/**\n * Convert SOL to lamports\n */\nexport function SOLToLamports(sol: number): bigint {\n  return BigInt(Math.floor(sol * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL));\n}\n\n/**\n * Format a balance for display with $ prefix\n */\nexport function formatBalanceDisplay(\n  lamports: number | bigint | null,\n  options: {\n    precision?: number;\n    showSymbol?: boolean;\n    compact?: boolean;\n  } = {}\n): string {\n  const { precision = 4, showSymbol = true, compact = false } = options;\n\n  if (lamports === null) {\n    return showSymbol ? \"$-.----\" : \"-.----\";\n  }\n\n  const formatted = compact\n    ? formatAmountCompact(lamports)\n    : formatAmount(lamports, precision);\n\n  return showSymbol ? `$${formatted}` : formatted;\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse a dollar amount string to lamports\n * Returns null if invalid\n */\nexport function parseSOLInput(input: string): bigint | null {\n  const trimmed = input.trim().replace(/,/g, \"\");\n  const value = parseFloat(trimmed);\n\n  if (isNaN(value) || value < 0) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return SOLToLamports(value);\n}\n\n/**\n * Validate if a string is a valid amount\n */\nexport function isValidSOLAmount(input: string): boolean {\n  return parseSOLInput(input) !== null;\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Balance formatting utilities. Handles SOL/lamports conversion, compact display formats, and input parsing/validation.\n\n---\n\n### 12. **packages/wallet/src/treasury/constants.ts**\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n// Fee constants (from ARCHITECTURE.md)\nexport const FEE_CONSTANTS = {\n  /** Total fee in basis points (300 = 3%) */\n  TOTAL_BPS: 300,\n  /** Platform revenue in basis points (200 = 2%) */\n  PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS: 200,\n  /** Cashback pool in basis points (50 = 0.5%) */\n  CASHBACK_POOL_BPS: 50,\n  /** Rewards budget in basis points (50 = 0.5%) */\n  REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS: 50,\n} as const;\n\n// Fee breakdown for display\nexport const FEE_BREAKDOWN = {\n  total: { bps: 300, display: \"3%\" },\n  platformRevenue: { bps: 200, display: \"2%\" },\n  cashbackPool: { bps: 50, display: \"0.5%\" },\n  rewardsBudget: { bps: 50, display: \"0.5%\" },\n} as const;\n\n// Hard limits from architecture (cannot be changed on-chain)\nexport const LIMITS = {\n  /** Maximum fee in basis points (1000 = 10%) */\n  MAX_FEE_BPS: 1000,\n  /** Maximum bet in lamports (1000 SOL) */\n  MAX_BET_LAMPORTS: 1_000_000_000_000n,\n  /** Maximum players per round */\n  MAX_PLAYERS_PER_ROUND: 10_000,\n} as const;\n\n// Placeholder program IDs - update with deployed addresses\nexport const PROGRAM_IDS = {\n  /** Pool manager program ID */\n  POOL_MANAGER: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  /** VRF consumer program ID */\n  VRF_CONSUMER: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  /** Game config program ID */\n  GAME_CONFIG: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n} as const;\n\n// Treasury addresses - update with deployed addresses\nexport const TREASURY_ADDRESSES = {\n  mainnet: {\n    treasury: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    rakeback: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    referral: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  },\n  devnet: {\n    treasury: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    rakeback: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n    referral: new PublicKey(\"11111111111111111111111111111111\"),\n  },\n} as const;\n\n/**\n * Calculate fee amount from pool total\n */\nexport function calculateFee(poolTotalLamports: bigint): bigint {\n  return (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.TOTAL_BPS)) / 10000n;\n}\n\n/**\n * Calculate winner payout from pool total (after fees)\n */\nexport function calculatePayout(poolTotalLamports: bigint): bigint {\n  const fee = calculateFee(poolTotalLamports);\n  return poolTotalLamports - fee;\n}\n\n/**\n * Calculate fee breakdown from pool total\n */\nexport function calculateFeeBreakdown(poolTotalLamports: bigint): {\n  total: bigint;\n  platformRevenue: bigint;\n  cashbackPool: bigint;\n  rewardsBudget: bigint;\n} {\n  const total = calculateFee(poolTotalLamports);\n  const platformRevenue =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.PLATFORM_REVENUE_BPS)) / 10000n;\n  const cashbackPool =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.CASHBACK_POOL_BPS)) / 10000n;\n  const rewardsBudget =\n    (poolTotalLamports * BigInt(FEE_CONSTANTS.REWARDS_BUDGET_BPS)) / 10000n;\n\n  return {\n    total,\n    platformRevenue,\n    cashbackPool,\n    rewardsBudget,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Treasury and fee configuration. Defines V1 3% fee split, limits, program IDs, and treasury addresses. Includes fee calculation helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 13. **packages/wallet/package.json**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/wallet\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n    \"./mock\": \"./src/mock/index.ts\",\n    \"./real\": \"./src/real/index.ts\",\n    \"./test\": \"./src/test/index.ts\",\n    \"./context\": \"./src/context.ts\",\n    \"./hooks\": {\n      \"import\": \"./src/hooks.ts\",\n      \"types\": \"./src/hooks.ts\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@jup-ag/wallet-adapter\": \"^0.2.6\",\n    \"@solana/wallet-adapter-base\": \"^0.9.23\",\n    \"@solana/wallet-adapter-react\": \"^0.15.35\",\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.3.1\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/react\": \"^18.3.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vite\": \"^6.0.0\"\n  },\n  \"peerDependencies\": {\n    \"react\": \"^18.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Package metadata and dependencies. Key exports allow selective imports (mock, real, test, hooks, context).\n\n---\n\n### 14. **packages/wallet/src/hooks.ts**\n```typescript\n// Lightweight hooks entry point - no provider dependencies\nexport { useWallet } from \"./useWallet\";\nexport { useBalance } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { BalanceResult } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { WalletState, WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Clean hooks export path. No provider dependencies, lightweight imports.\n\n---\n\n### 15. **packages/wallet/src/index.ts**\n```typescript\n// Context (standalone - no provider dependencies)\nexport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\n\n// Core hooks (import context, not providers)\nexport { useWallet } from \"./useWallet\";\nexport { useBalance } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { WalletState, WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\n// Mock wallet exports (lightweight - no adapter dependency)\nexport { MockWalletProvider, DEFAULT_MOCK_CONFIG } from \"./mock\";\nexport type { MockConfig } from \"./mock\";\n\n// Real wallet exports (lazy-loaded via WalletProvider, or direct import)\nexport { RealWalletProvider } from \"./real\";\n\n// Test wallet exports (for E2E against local test-validator)\nexport { TestWalletProvider } from \"./test\";\n\n// Full wallet provider\nexport { WalletProvider } from \"./WalletProvider\";\n\n// Balance utilities\nexport { solToLamports, lamportsToSol } from \"./mock\";\nexport {\n  formatAmount,\n  formatAmountCompact,\n  lamportsToSOL,\n  SOLToLamports,\n  formatBalanceDisplay,\n  parseSOLInput,\n  isValidSOLAmount,\n} from \"./balance\";\nexport type { BalanceResult } from \"./useBalance\";\n\n// Transaction management\nexport {\n  TransactionProvider,\n  useTransaction,\n} from \"./transactions\";\nexport type {\n  TransactionState,\n  TransactionStatus,\n  TransactionContextValue,\n} from \"./transactions\";\n\n// Treasury utilities\nexport {\n  FEE_CONSTANTS,\n  FEE_BREAKDOWN,\n  LIMITS,\n  PROGRAM_IDS,\n  TREASURY_ADDRESSES,\n  calculateFee,\n  calculatePayout,\n  calculateFeeBreakdown,\n} from \"./treasury\";\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Main export barrel. Carefully curated to allow tree-shaking and selective imports.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architecture Insights\n\n1. **Three Wallet Modes**:\n   - **Mock** (default): Fully in-memory, no RPC needed, persists to localStorage\n   - **Real**: Jupiter Unified Wallet Adapter, real RPC connection\n   - **Test**: Hardwired Keypair for E2E testing against local validator\n\n2. **Environment-Driven Switching**:\n   - `VITE_MOCK_MODE` (defaults to `true`) controls router\n   - `VITE_RPC_URL` for real wallet RPC endpoint\n   - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` for cluster selection (defaults to devnet)\n\n3. **Context Pattern**:\n   - Single `WalletContext` shared across all providers\n   - Minimal interface (`WalletContextValue`)\n   - Hooks (`useWallet`, `useBalance`) provide safe access\n\n4. **Balance Polling**:\n   - Automatic polling (configurable interval)\n   - Supports both mock and real wallets\n   - Manual refresh method\n\n5. **Transaction Tracking**:\n   - State machine (`idle` → `signing` → `submitting` → `confirming` → `confirmed`/`failed`)\n   - Separate provider for async transaction submission\n\n6. **Treasury Constants**:\n   - 3% total fee (2% platform, 0.5% cashback, 0.5% rewards)\n   - Placeholder program IDs and addresses (pending deployment)"}],"totalDurationMs":75732,"totalTokens":49470,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3682,"cache_read_input_tokens":36018,"output_tokens":9764,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3682,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
